Cell[TextData[{
 "What different variables mean:\[LineSeparator]M - mass of Delta\
\[LineSeparator]MN - mass of Nucleon\[LineSeparator]\[CapitalGamma] - Delta\
\[CloseCurlyQuote]s decay width (I had to set it to some value to relax the s \
channel divergence) \[CapitalGamma] = 117 MeV\[LineSeparator]fPi - ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["f", "\[Pi]"], " ", "=", " ", 
    RowBox[{"93", "MeV"}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "dfca6d9a-ab04-214c-a4e9-c06d18a47a87"],
 "\ngD - the coupling from The Book, Eq. 4.202. Should be about gD = ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    FractionBox["3", "5"], 
    SqrtBox["2"], "gA"}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "51e86632-551d-8947-9fed-7f6e86c7edd3"],
 " = 1.07\[LineSeparator]gDGI - so far unknown in value. Some reasonable \
values I found are ~0.17 looking just by eye\[LineSeparator]\nAccording to \
https://www.hepdata.net/record/ins44234, the charged pion nucleon elastic \
cross section is 16mb at ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"energies", " ", 
    SqrtBox["s"]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "0e37a08a-0f20-f74c-a3c4-c9d0d075f09d"],
 "~1.75GeV This lead me to estimate gDGI~0.2045 and gD~0.4\[LineSeparator]\
\[LineSeparator]The GI coupling does seem to increase the total cross section \
more quickly (cross section blows up ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"with", " ", "W"}], "=", 
    RowBox[{
     SqrtBox["s"], "."}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "78cec0bb-830c-684b-9103-612466473881"],
 ")"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.978063906177332*^9, 3.978064249737532*^9}, {
  3.9780642941952667`*^9, 3.978064419439481*^9}, {3.978064500808668*^9, 
